<div class="header">
<h1>River Phoenix</h1>
    </div>
<div class="image" id="img-div" img caption="River Phoenix">
<img src="https://media.nbcdfw.com/2019/09/River-Phoenix.jpg?fit=722%2C406" alt="photo of river phoenix" id="image">
  <figcaption>"In simplicity there is truth." -RJP
  </figcaption>
</div "image">
  <br>
  <br>
<p1 id="tribute-info" class="body">
  River Jude Phoenix wore many hats during his 23 years on Earth. A talented actor, <br> musician, animal rights activist, and teen hearthrob, River captivated the 80s on <br> and off stage. Rivers impact can be felt through just about anyone he had ever met. Revered by those who <br>knew him as a truly special soul, River aimed to bring harmony and healing to the world in anyway he knew how.
  </p1>
  <br>
  <br>
<br>
 <ul id="timeline">
   <li><b>1970:</b> River Jude Phoenix is born to Arlyn Dunetz and John Lee Bottom </li>
   <br>
   <br>
   <li><b>1973:</b> Dunetz and Bottom join the Children of God religious cult<br> Claims of River and his siblings being abused during the family's time in <br>Children of God are debated</li>
  <br>
   <br>
   <li><b>1973:</b> Dunetz and Bottom join the Children of God religious cult<br> Claims of River and his siblings being abused during the family's time in <br>Children of God are debated</li>
   <br>
   <br>
   <li><b>1980:</b> River begins pursuing a career in acting alongside his sister Rain</li>
   <br>
   <br>
   <li><b>1986:</b> River gets his big break into film with the debut of "Stand By Me"<br> in a role that would go on to connect with people for decades after his passing</li>
   <br>
   <br>
   <li><b>1987:</b> River and his sister Rain form "Aleka's Attic" a band that <br>specialized in "progressive, ethereal folk-rock" in River's words</li>
   <br>
   <br>
   <li><b>1992:</b> River receives the Humanitarian Award for his PETA fundraising efforts</li>
   <br>
   <br>
   <li><b>1993:</b> On Halloween night, River Phoneix dies of an overdose <br>outside of the Viper Room in Los Angeles
  </ul>
  <br>
  <p2 id="ending">
    River's spirit touched all who had the divine pleasure of meeting him. <br>Friends and family contest he was a man of his word who fought endlessly for what he believed in. <br>His story continues to inspire after nearly 3 decades since his passing. <br>Though his life was cut short, his impact is neverending.
    <br>
